13T18:40:32Z", "closed_at": "2017-01-13T18:40:32Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "body_html": "<p>The <code>nn.LSTM</code> module gives different output between CPU and GPU mode when <code>batch_first=True</code>; in CPU mode its output has shape (batch_size, sequence_length, hidden_dim) but in GPU mode its output has shape (sequence_length, batch_size, hidden_dim). Here's a test case:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://gist.github.com/jcjohnson/ce3e000696c845d7e62fc8554e8cd884\">https://gist.github.com/jcjohnson/ce3e000696c845d7e62fc8554e8cd884</a></p>\n<p>This gives the following output:</p>\n<pre><code>Here is output in CPU mode:\n(16L, 100L, 256L)\n(3L, 16L, 256L)\n(3L, 16L, 256L)\nHere is output in GPU mode:\n(100L, 16L, 256L)\n(3L, 16L, 256L)\n(3L, 16L, 256L)\n</code></pre>", "body_text": "The nn.LSTM module gives different output between CPU and GPU mode when batch_first=True; in CPU mode its output has shape (batch_size, sequence_length, hidden_dim) but in GPU mode its output has shape (sequence_length, batch_size, hidden_dim). Here's a test case:\nhttps://gist.github.com/jcjohnson/ce3e000696c845d7e62fc8554e8cd884\nThis gives the following output:\nHere is output in CPU mode:\n(16L, 100L, 256L)\n(3L, 16L, 256L)\n(3L, 16L, 256L)\nHere is output in GPU mode:\n(100L, 16L, 256L)\n(3L, 16L, 256L)\n(3L, 16L, 256L)", "body": "The `nn.LSTM` module gives different output between CPU and GPU mode when `batch_first=True`; in CPU mode its output has shape (batch_size, sequence_length, hidden_dim) but in GPU mode its output has shape (sequence_length, batch_size, hidden_dim). Here's a test case:\r\n\r\nhttps://gist.github.com/jcjohnson/ce3e000696c845d7e62fc8554e8cd884\r\n\r\nThis gives the following output:\r\n\r\n```\r\nHere is output in CPU mode:\r\n(16L, 100L, 256L)\r\n(3L, 16L, 256L)\r\n(3L, 16L, 256L)\r\nHere is output in GPU mode:\r\n(100L, 16L, 256L)\r\n(3L, 16L, 256L)\r\n(3L, 16L, 256L)\r\n```"}